# H2SO4 Advanced Functional Library

A modular, high-performance extension package for the **H2SO4** programming language runtime. This library introduces essential functional programming paradigms—such as lazy collection mapping, filtering, reducing, and micro-benchmarking—powered directly by native TypeScript acceleration under the hood.

---

## Features

* **`range(start, end[, step])`**: Generates a numerical array safely within engine bounds.
* **`map(array, callback)`**: Transforms collection elements using custom H2SO4 closures.
* **`filter(array, predicate)`**: Filters arrays dynamically based on conditional logic.
* **`reduce(array, callback, initialValue)`**: Accumulates array values into a single condensed runtime type.
* **`benchmark(callback, iterations)`**: A high-precision utility for tracking execution speed in microseconds.

---

## Project Structure

The library is strictly decoupled into independent, single-responsibility files:

```text
Advanced/
├── utils.ts        # Shared callback invoker and ReturnSignal interceptor
├── range.ts        # Fast array generator
├── map.ts          # Inline array mapping transformer
├── filter.ts       # Collection pruning engine
├── reduce.ts       # Sequential accumulator engine
├── benchmark.ts    # Performance profiling system
└── mod.ts          # Central module aggregator and registration entry-point
